  aim: "Speech compression at 4.8–16 kbps with natural-sounding quality by using a codebook to represent the excitation signal.",
  complexity: "Analysis-by-synthesis: encoder searches the codebook exhaustively, O(N·C) per subframe, where C = codebook size. Decoder O(N·p).",
  strengths: "Far more natural than LPC vocoders; flexible bitrate; became the basis for nearly all modern speech codecs.",
